⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Great King of Terror
node N1 · N1 · ⟦The Great King of Terror:N1:1a5548⟧

WHO   — The Great King of Terror — the dread quatrain
WHAT  — The most date-certain and most-feared line in the whole prophetic corpus — a quatrain that fixed a year, and so seized the imagination of five centuries; the emblem of the apocalyptic reading of Nostradamus.
WHERE — N1 · Nostradamus  Framework inputs: Les Propheties (1555)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a prophecy with a date is a prophecy you can fear by the calendar; because the brevity and the named month made it irresistible to doomsayers; and because the year came and went, it is also the emblem of the prophecy that did not arrive.
HOW   — By a cryptic French quatrain dense with omen — sky, terror, a great king, a king of the Mongols, Mars before and after — left open enough that any catastrophe could be poured into it, and any failure explained away.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I named a year so the fear could be measured — and the year passed, and I am the proof that a date can outlive its own undoing.

spoken token : laem-kaer-stein   ·   hex : 1a5548
